    "course_title": "POLITICAL AND CULTURAL PERSPECTIVES IN DANCE STUDIES",
    "description": "Examines the role of dance as a cultural form of expression within the political sphere. Draws on a variety of case studies ranging from popular dance TV shows, to European modern dance and from hip-hop to dancing at public protests and asks the question of what constitutes dance and what is its social and political function.",
